  "prompt": "What is the oldest book ever written?",
  "response": "The oldest known book is generally considered to be \"The Epic of Gilgamesh,\" which dates back to around 2100 BCE. It is an ancient Mesopotamian epic poem written on clay tablets in cuneiform script. The story revolves around the heroic deeds and adventures of Gilgamesh, the king of Uruk, and explores themes of friendship, the quest for immortality, and the nature of humanity. There are older writings, such as various religious texts, inscriptions, and administrative documents, but \"The Epic of Gilgamesh\" is often regarded as the oldest known narrative literary work.",
